I made the dish by the recipe, only I doubled it. Two sets of guests praised the dish and asked for the recipe. I do not agree with the previous negative review, as I saw no hidden pitfalls. Though like hollandaise in flavor, this is NOT a true hollandaise, but I had no problem executing it using the difections given. The first time I refrigerated overnight in the refrigerator then cooked for brunch. The second time I poured the liquid over the muffins, etc. and froze the dish immediately. I thawed in the refrigerator overnight, then cooked 30 minutes. I preferred the consistency of this one to the first, as this one retained more of the muffin texture and was less like a pudding.

